# DAC permissions for the serial GPS device nodes so the HAL (user gps) can
# open them. SELinux labelling is separate — see sepolicy/file_contexts.
#
# APEXes cannot carry ueventd rules (ueventd only reads /system, /vendor and
# /odm etc/ueventd.rc), so APPEND these lines to your device tree's ueventd
# file — the one installed as /vendor/etc/ueventd.rc, e.g.:
#   emulator: the goldfish ueventd rc (grep -rln ueventd device/generic/goldfish)
#   rpi:      the ueventd rc in device/brcm/rpi4 / rpi5
# Trim to your board's actual GPS tty if you don't want every serial port
# gps-owned.
/dev/ttyO*      0660   gps   system
/dev/ttyS*      0660   gps   system
/dev/ttyUSB*    0660   gps   system
/dev/ttyACM*    0660   gps   system
/dev/ttyAMA*    0660   gps   system
